<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="62" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1438,151,476]" pageId="5" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,339,301,327]" pageId="5" pageNumber="62">Etymology.</emphasis>
The generic name 
<taxonomicName box="[564,697,301,326]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Aeginidae" genus="Bathykorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Narcomedusae" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[564,697,301,326]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="62">Bathykorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
references the habitat and shape of the species. 
<emphasis box="[1270,1338,301,326]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="62">Bathy</emphasis>
(Greek; from 
<emphasis box="[216,295,338,363]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="62">bathus</emphasis>
, depth or deep) refers to the deep-sea habitat of the species, and 
<emphasis box="[1068,1133,338,363]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="62">korus</emphasis>
(Greek; helmet) refers to the helmet-like shape of the bell. The specific epithet of 
<taxonomicName box="[856,966,376,401]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Aeginidae" genus="Bathykorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Narcomedusae" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="bouilloni">
<emphasis box="[856,966,376,401]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="62">bouilloni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is named in honor of the late Dr. Jean Bouillon, (
<number box="[278,418,413,439]" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" value="1967.5" valueMax="2009.0" valueMin="1926.0">
<date box="[278,418,413,439]" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" value="1926" valueMax="2009">1926–2009</date>
</number>
). Dr. Bouillon’s studies spanned over 
<number box="[877,907,413,439]" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" value="60.0">60</number>
years, and described 
<number box="[1164,1193,413,439]" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" value="17.0">17</number>
families, 
<number box="[1312,1341,413,439]" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" value="34.0">34</number>
genera, and 
<number box="[200,243,450,476]" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" value="114.0">114</number>
species. His work and his generous sprit continue to enlighten and inspire generations of biologists.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
